<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">TRHYPOCHTHONIIDAE</taxonomicName>
Willmann, 1931
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
At first (Berlese, 1896b) 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hypochthoniidae" genus="Hypochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tectorum">Hypochthonius tectorum Berlese</taxonomicName>
(1896) was classified with the 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nothridae</taxonomicName>
, later (Berlese, 1910) is was considered one of the representatives of the family 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hypochthoniidae" genus="Hypochthoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hypochthoniidae</taxonomicName>
. Willmann (1931) created the 
<taxonomicName pageId="71" pageNumber="72" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Trhypochthoniinae">Trhypochthoniinae</taxonomicName>
, a subfamily of the 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hypochthoniidae" genus="Hypochthoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hypochthoniidae</taxonomicName>
, which afterwards has been regarded as a separate family; it is related to the 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Malaconothridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Malaconothridae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
Berlese's species are classified here with the genera 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" genus="Trhypochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trhypochthonius</taxonomicName>
Berlese. 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" genus="Trhypochthoniellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trhypochthoniellus</taxonomicName>
Willmann, and Allonothrus Van der Hammen 1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
1) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="KnÃ¼lle" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Knuelle</normalizedToken>
(1957, p. 150) created a separate family 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trhypochthoniellidae</taxonomicName>
, because the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" genus="Trhypochthoniellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trhypochthoniellus</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" genus="Trhypochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trhypochthonius</taxonomicName>
as well as from the 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Malaconothridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Malaconothridae</taxonomicName>
. Recently (Van der Hammen, 1955, 1955a), while dealing with the genera 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" genus="Archegozetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Archegozetes</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" genus="Allonothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Allonothrus</taxonomicName>
, I demonstrated, however, that it is difficult to divide the family 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Trhypochthoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trhypochthoniidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
